          • [ - ] Xsim - member since 01-Dec-12

            I believe Real Madrid will look more comfortable playing in front their crowd. Most importantly, Karim Benzema, providing he starts will give a threat to the attacking line. His unselfishness will provide a moral boost to his teammates, Bale and Ronaldo more specifically, in which after the first game is much needed. This game in many ways can hurt Madrid if another draw would to occur. Rafa has done some interesting experimentation in the first game, something I believe he will carry on throughout the season. His rotation policy will definitely benefit the team however if they don't start clicking this early, it would be a useless policy come around the second half of the season. It's easy to point fingers after a mediocre or below par performance with a team of Real's calibre; in previous seasons, goals let in by Iker, now the "lack of goals" (including some games during preseason). Truth be told, the alteration of management and constant change of philosophy is to blame.
